"FILES*" DISSOLVE (CR)
.SKIP 1
"DISSOLVE        DISSOLVE THE DISK STRUCTURE FOR DSKB."
"                REMOVE ALL UNITS FROM THE SYSTEM STRUCTURE."
.SKIP 1
^&"ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO DO THIS?"\& YES OR NO (CR)
.SKIP 1
"FILES*"DEFINE (CR)
.PARA
.FILL.JUST
THIS COMMAND IS USED WHEN FIRST BRINGING UP A SYSTEM WITH A BLANK SET
OF PACKS.  IT ASKS WHICH PACKS BELONG IN THE STRUCTURE BEING DEFINED.
IT WILL SET THE PARMETERS FOR THAT STRUCTURE AND FOR ALL THE UNITS PUT
INTO THAT STRUCTURE TO STANDARD VALUES.  IF THE PACKS ARE REALLY BLANK,
IT MAY ASK FOR UNIT ID'S FOR SOME OF THE UNITS.  IF THIS IS NECESSARY,
THE NAME OF THE UNIT WILL BE PRINTED BEFORE THE QUESTION IS ASKED.
.NOTE
IF AN OLD STRUCTURE EXISTS, IT MUST BE DISSOLVED BEFORE IT CAN BE RE-DEFINED.
.END NOTE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
"TYPE NAMES OF PHYSICAL UNITS IN STR, EXTRA CR WHEN DONE"
BPA0 (CR)  (THESE ARE TYPED IN BY OPERATOR)
BPA1 (CR)
BPA2 (CR) (CR)
.SKIP 1
"FILES*"REFRESH (CR)
.PARA
THIS COMMAND IS USED TO REFRESH A FILE STRUCTURE.  IT IS NORMALLY
ONLY USED WHEN A FILE STRUCTURE IS BEING BUILT ON A FRESH SET OF
PACKS.
.SKIP 1
"REFRESH        REFRESH THE STRUCTURE."
"               ERASE THE CURRENT FILE SYSTEM AND START OVER"
"               WITH A FRESH DISK."
