<ZFORMAT (LIST)
.PARA
^ZERO OUT ALL ALTERNATE TRACK ASSIGNMENTS.  ^THIS COMMAND WIPES OUT
ANY PREVIOUS BAD TRACK INFORMATION AND FORMATS THE ENTIRE PACK,
INCLUDING ALTERNATE CYLINDERS.
.PARA
^THIS COMMAND ESTABLISHES THE CORRECT FORMAT ON A PACK.
^THE FORMAT COMMAND CALLS THE <AFORMAT COMMAND.  ^IT ALSO CALLS THE
<VERIFY COMMAND WHEN IT HAS FINISHED TO INSURE THAT THE
FORMAT HAS BEEN CORRECTLY SET. ^IF <PAKCOP BELIEVES THAT THE
PACK IS ALREADY FORMATTED, IT WILL ASK:
^^
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.SKIP 1
'UNIT 300 ALREADY FORMATTED, REFORMAT?'
.PARA
