.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
.PARA
   ^After the ^System is down, and it is at the <"BOOTS" prompt, load in the
<"PACKCOPY" version from disk.
^The <"PACKCOPY" program <PAKCP5 should be called before taking the disk
<UNITS off-line.
^If not, the program will have to be
loaded via tape.  ^It may be
helpful to list out the <"HELP" commands after entering the date, time, and
after the status of <UNITs prints out.
.SKIP 1
.INDEX <PAKCOP <DISK <UNIT <STATUS
.LM 7
.CENTER;^&<CHECKING <DISK <UNIT <STATUS\&
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
^Before performing a <"PACKCOPY", you need to put the unit
to be copied to <"ON-LINE" and in <"READ/WRITE" mode.  ^All other <"UNITS"
^&must\& be put in <"READ <ONLY" mode.
.SKIP 1
.CENTER;^&<PUTTING <ONE <UNIT <ON-LINE\&
.SKIP 1
^Go to the back of the module, and after opening the double doors,
locate the panel that has <"CE <MODE" and <"SERVICE <BYPASS" on it.  ^You
will be working with the toggle switch under <"CE <MODE" only.  
.SKIP 1
^If <UNIT is <OFF-LINE, move <"CE <MODE" toggle switch to middle and then
push <"ATTENTION" button on <UNIT to put it <"ON-LINE".
.SKIP 1
.CENTER;^&<PUTTING <ONE <UNIT <OFF-LINE\&
.SKIP 1
^To take <UNIT <"OFF-LINE", move <"CE <MODE" switch in direction of <UNIT
you want <"OFF-LINE".
.SKIP 1
.CENTER;^&<PUTTING <BOTH <UNITS <(MODULE) <OFF-LINE\&
.SKIP 1
^Toggle <"CE <MODE" switch to <"A" then <"B", then return to middle.
^Both <UNITs are now <"OFF-LINE".
.NOTE
.CENTER;* * * * * <C <A <U <T <I <O <N * * * * *
.SKIP 1
^IF THE <"CE <MODE" switch is left in either position, <"A" or <"B",
that <UNIT cannot be brought <"ON-LINE" until the switch is moved to
the <"MIDDLE".
.END NOTE
